Former President George H.W. Bush congratulates President Obama for remembering the 19th anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act. He emphasizes that there is no place for prejudice in society and acknowledges that disabled Americans were not given equal rights and opportunities in the past. Bush highlights the accomplishments of the ADA, such as improved accessibility in sports events, public transportation, and workplaces. However, he also emphasizes that there is still work to be done and encourages everyone to continue striving for equality and inclusion.